Description:

```
Software is like the weather, it's always changing!

Remote server: nc challs.xmas.htsp.ro 12002
Files: folder
Author: littlewho
```

Upon connecting to the server, something similar is received

```
$: ncat challs.xmas.htsp.ro 12002
The weather is so unpredictable... Let me give you a binary to play with
Content: b''



What's your name?
```

The binaries are always different and automation must be done. All binaries however have a similar vulnerability, namely
a stack based buffer overflow.

A `Dockerfile` is provided via the website to hint at the version of libc that is used.
